{"type":"message","id":"8c9e4c4c","parentId":"535faadd","timestamp":"2026-02-18T12:12:24.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Pinpointing the Repository**\n\nThe search continues, but the root and initial subdirectories have proved fruitless.  The `SOUL.md` file reveals a crucial piece of information, identifying the target repository.  This leads me to consider the most effective approach - leveraging the GitHub API directly, given the current context.\n\n\n**Checking API Authentication**\n\nI've got the repository name from `SOUL.md`: `franklinbaldo/aparicio-funes`. Since I'm considering direct API access via `gh`, I need to confirm the authentication status first. Then, I'll aim to list the pull requests using `gh pr list --repo`. Using `gh` seems like the best next move.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771416744942_16","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh auth status"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":721,"output":157,"cacheRead":4379,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5257,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771416738884}}
